==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Micrography
<hw>Mi*crog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets> + <ets>-graphy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>micrographie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The description of
microscopic objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Examination or study by means of the microscope, as
of an etched surface of metal to determine its structure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Microhm</ent>⟦br⟧
